## Learning Metamagic

Wizards learn metamagic options through advances, similar to how fighters learn combat techniques:

**Starting Metamagic:** Most wizards begin with 1-2 metamagic options. These represent the techniques learned during magical training—the foundations of your metamagic mastery.

**Advancement Progression:** When spending advances, wizards can choose to learn additional metamagic options instead of other advancement choices. By campaign end (Legendary rank), experienced wizards might know 4-6 metamagic techniques.

**No Archetype Restriction:** Only wizards can learn metamagic through their class feature, but the specific techniques chosen are personal preference. Two wizards with identical spell lists play completely differently based on metamagic selections.

