## Metamagic by Purpose

### Damage Enhancement

**Heighten** increases spell damage beyond base values. Use when you need to eliminate tough enemies quickly or overcome damage resistance. The extra Momentum investment pays off against dangerous foes.

**Empower** maximizes certain dice results. Use when you need consistency over variable damage. Reliable damage matters more against precision targets than maximum potential damage.

### Tactical Modification

**Widen** affects larger areas. Use when facing multiple clustered enemies. The increased area can hit 2-3 additional targets, multiplying spell effectiveness.

**Extend** increases duration for ongoing effects. Use on buffs (Shield, Blur) or persistent battlefield control. Longer duration means fewer recasts, conserving spell slots and Momentum.

**Quicken** reduces casting time. Use when action economy matters—casting and moving in the same turn, responding instantly to threats, or maintaining combat tempo.

### Subtle Casting

**Subtle** makes spellcasting less obvious. Use in social situations where you can't be seen casting, or combat scenarios where enemies target visible spellcasters. The stealth value exceeds the Momentum cost in many situations.

