## Game Master Guidance

### Teaching Metamagic

Don't require extensive training time or special teachers. Wizards learn metamagic through advances like any other advancement. You can flavor this as:
- Self-discovery through experimentation
- Insights from spellbooks or scrolls
- Refinement of technique through practice
- Guidance from mentors during downtime

But don't gatekeep metamagic behind narrative requirements that delay mechanical advancement.

### Balancing Enhanced Spells

Metamagic makes wizards more powerful but not overwhelmingly so:
- Momentum costs limit frequency (can't enhance every spell)
- Stacking costs limit combinations (triple-enhanced spells rare)
- Other spellcasters have different advantages (Cleric domains, Bard inspiration)

Don't punish wizards for using metamagic effectively. If they spend Momentum wisely to win fights, that's working as intended.

### Metamagic in Different Campaigns

**High Magic:** Wizards might start with 3 metamagic options, learn more frequently. Metamagic becomes defining feature from beginning.

**Standard Magic:** Wizards start with 1-2 options, learn more at Seasoned/Veteran ranks. Metamagic develops over campaign.

**Low Magic:** Wizards might have only 1-2 metamagic options total. Limited enhancement options reflect rare magical knowledge.

### Common Questions

**Can non-wizards learn metamagic?**
No. Metamagic is the wizard's unique subsystem, like fighter techniques or rogue gambits. Other spellcasters have their own unique features.

**Can wizards apply metamagic to all spells?**
Yes, unless specific metamagic has limitations. Most metamagic works with any spell.

**Do metamagic costs stack with spell costs?**
Yes. Enhanced spells cost base spell Momentum + metamagic Momentum. Heightened Fireball (-1 base, -1 metamagic) costs -2 total.

**Can wizards learn unlimited metamagic?**
No. Limit based on advances invested. Typical wizard might know 4-6 options by Legendary rank.

